transcript.text: Hi, I'm Magnus, I'm the CTO of Church and in Denmark.
I met Reddicks 3 months ago.
By coincidence we were exploring the market for some we've enabled print shops.
We came across on print shop and the company's CEO was the one who actually found the software on the Internet.
I've been into IT industry for the last 10 years now.
I've been working a lot in India, faced a lot of difficulties.
So when I first met up with Radix, it was more like exploiting the on friendship.
But it turned out that Radix is much more than just the on friendship.
Actually Radix is a splendid IT company.
So right now we're actually placing a lot of system, a lot of development effort is done from from Radix team right now.

And the big difference between the the past two companies that we've been working with is that this company really implements everything about structures and processes which are quite important for us in order to get our stuff done.
So we actually experience now that we get twice the quality in half the time what we got earlier.

OK, after meeting Raddatz for the first time, they told me a lot about the business processes and the way that they practice process over people compared to where I come from, that is something that I would never do.
So I thought that if they do this, they might leave out all the creativityness or all the individualism of of all their employees.
So it was quite a experience when I came to the office to find that all the employees are very fond of what they do.
We went to this conference room, we had a couple of developers coming up and showing what they were waiting on right now.
And it was like they were bringing the small kids to the scene.
They were very fond of of everything they did there.
So I actually experienced a lot of creativeness and and a lot of a lot of dedication to what they do.
And that is something that goes through the entire organization.
One thing to say about Radics is just the same that you would say about India.
It's quite hard to explain.
It has to be experienced.
